(n\tau + X) \sim \mathcal{G}(n, \lambda)
n, \tau
f(y) = \frac{\lambda^n}{\Gamma(n)} y^{n-1}e^{-\lambda y}
Y = g(X)
f(y) = f(g^{-1}(y))
g^{-1}(y) = y - n \tau
f(y) = f(g^{-1}(y)) = \frac{\lambda^n}{\Gamma(n)}(y-n\tau)^{n-1}e^{-\lambda(y-n\tau)}
